            "product_text_content_1": "<p>The neoprene used to make the double loop <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Deadlift-Lifting-Lifters-Weightlifters-Workout/dp/B08CXGDGQ5/?tag=wbcmb-20\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.amazon.com/Deadlift-Lifting-Lifters-Weightlifters-Workout/dp/B08CXGDGQ5/?tag=wbcmb-20\">lifting straps</a> is better than what you’d usually find. Especially when you consider the affordable price. It doesn't seem to fray or break plus the reinforced stitching on the seams and pads are strong indicators that these will last quite a bit of time.</p><p>The pads make a lot of difference comfort-wise, although they're not the thickest I've ever seen. If they were a bit thicker it would make them a lot more comfortable without having it influence the functionality of the straps.</p><p>There are three sizes available. If you have smaller wrists but are interested in them because of the price, ensure that the minimum size will be the correct fit for your wrist. This is due to these straps having slightly different wrist sizes compared to some of the others on the list. Consult the wrist size chart above in the specifications table.</p><p>Size large has a lot of give when you grip the bar. With that in mind, the size L is closer to extra large than your regular large.</p>",
